programme.sub-title: Tennessee Titans at Kansas City Chiefs
programme.desc: Tennessee Titans (9-7) at Kansas City Chiefs (10-6) in an AFC wild-card game. From Arrowhead Stadium. K.C. boasts NFL rushing king Kareem Hunt and a plus-14 home turnover ratio. QB Marcus Mariota and the Titans pulled out a 19-17 win here in Dec. 2016, getting a walk-off 53-yard field goal from ex-Chief Ryan Succop. K.C. has dropped its last five home playoff games (last won after 1993 season), while Tennessee is making its first postseason appearance in nine years. (cc)

programme.desc: Atlanta Falcons (10-6) at Los Angeles Rams (11-5) in an NFC wild-card game. From Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum. Dan Quinn's defending NFC champs bring a 5-3 road record to the first L.A. playoff game in 24 years, the Rams' first anywhere since 2004-05, when they lost by 30 in Atlanta. The NFC's rushing leader (Todd Gurley) and receiving yards leader (Julio Jones) are on display. (cc)
